LS (Wizard Command)
===================

Usage: ls [path]

List the contents of a directory in the mudlib.

Arguments:
  [path]  - Optional path to list (defaults to current wizard's home)

Examples:
  ls                          - List your home directory
  ls /world/rooms            - List the rooms directory
  ls /std                    - List the standard library

Notes:
  - Requires Wizard or higher access level
  - Shows files and directories
  - Paths are relative to the mudlib root

See also: load, clone
